===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|choppen}}, variant of {{m|enm|chappen||to chop}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}}  {{m|ang|*ċeappian}}, {{m|ang|*ċieppan}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*kapp-}}, {{m|gem-pro|*kap-||to chop; cut; split}}. Akin to {{cog|stq|kappe}}, {{m|stq|kapje||to hack; chop; lop off}}, {{cog|nl|kappen||to chop, cut, hew}}, {{cog|gml|koppen||to cut off, lop, poll}}, German Low German {{m|nds-de|kappen||to cut off; clip}}, German {{m|de|kappen||to cut; clip}}, German dialectal {{m|de|chapfen||to chop into small pieces}}, {{cog|da|kappe||to cut, lop off, poll}}, {{cog|sv|kapa||to cut}}, Albanian {{m|sq|copë||piece, chunk}}, {{cog|ang|*ċippian}} (attested in {{m|ang|forċippian||to cut off}}). More at {{l|en|chip}}.

